First keep the following tutorials open somewhere: 
1. http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/tutorial
2. http://api.mongodb.org/python/current/


Depending on your GNU/Linux operating system and the way you choose to install the steps may vary


Install python-virtualenv if you have already not done so
Install virtualenvwrapper 

$mkvirtualenv fossevents
$pip install flask
$pip install pymongo

install Mongodb as root if not installed already

This app needs the following installed on your system
1. Python
2. Flask
3. Mongodb
4. Pymongo

Instructions:
1. Start 'mongod' from one shell
2. Start 'python index.py' from another
3. Your site is live at http://localhost:5000 -- enjoy
